(7, 'Knee joint', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\">The knee joint has three parts. The thigh\r\nbone (the femur) meets the large shin bone (the tibia) to form the main knee\r\njoint. This joint has an inner (medial) and an outer (lateral) compartment. The\r\nkneecap (the patella) joins the femur to form a third joint, called the\r\npatellofemoral joint. The patella protects the front of the knee joint.</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-hansi-font-family:Calibri\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-hansi-font-family:Calibri\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\">Investigation of knee injuries must be\r\nundertaken with care, as the symptoms can originate from\r\nthe&nbsp;lumbar&nbsp;spine. We will make a thorough investigation to discover\r\nthe cause and propose the correct treatment.</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-hansi-font-family:Calibri\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\">At CLINIC.CO.UK we have assessed and successfully\r\ntreated many patients with conditions including:</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:150%;mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-hansi-font-family:Calibri\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;background:yellow;\r\nmso-highlight:yellow\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir=\"LTR\"></span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow\">Osteoarthritis</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: &quot;Bookman Old Style&quot;, serif; background: yellow;\">: </span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"background:yellow;\r\nmso-highlight:yellow\">pain and inflammation caused by degeneration and\r\ndeterioration of the joint<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;background:yellow;\r\nmso-highlight:yellow\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir=\"LTR\"></span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow\">Tendinitis: pain in the front of\r\nthe knee which is made worse when climbing, taking stairs, or walking up an\r\nincline<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size: 10pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: Symbol; background: yellow;\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir=\"LTR\"></span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow\">Bursitis: inflammation caused by\r\nrepeated overuse or injury of the knee<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;background:yellow;\r\nmso-highlight:yellow\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir=\"LTR\"></span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow\">Chondromalacia Patella: damaged cartilage\r\nunder the kneecap<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;background:yellow;\r\nmso-highlight:yellow\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir=\"LTR\"></span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow\">Gout: arthritis caused by the build-up\r\nof uric acid <o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;background:yellow;\r\nmso-highlight:yellow\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir=\"LTR\"></span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow\">Baker’s Cyst: a build-up of synovial\r\nfluid (fluid that lubricates the joint) behind the knee<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;background:yellow;\r\nmso-highlight:yellow\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir=\"LTR\"></span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow\">Rheumatoid Arthritis: a chronic\r\nautoimmune inflammatory disorder that causes painful swelling and can eventually\r\ncause joint deformity and bone erosion<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;background:yellow;\r\nmso-highlight:yellow\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir=\"LTR\"></span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow\">Dislocation: dislocation of the\r\nkneecap most often the result of trauma<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;color:red;\r\nbackground:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir=\"LTR\"></span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow\">Meniscus Tear: a rupture in one\r\nor more of the cartilages in the knee. <b><i><span style=\"color:red\">How many are there?<o:p></o:p></span></i></b></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:list .5in\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:\r\n10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Symbol;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:Symbol;background:yellow;\r\nmso-highlight:yellow\">·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span dir=\"LTR\"></span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"background:yellow;mso-highlight:yellow\">Torn Ligament: a tear in one of\r\nthe four ligaments in the knee — the most commonly injured ligament is the Anterior\r\nCruciate Ligament (ACL) <b><i><span style=\"color:red\">If you are giving\r\nfull descriptions for these you should do the same for the others. </span></i></b><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><h3><span lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;Treatment&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></h3><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"background:yellow;mso-highlight:\r\nyellow\">(At our clinic we break down any of the above condition into tightness of\r\nsoft tissue in your&nbsp;quadriceps&nbsp;then we use the mothed of treatment of\r\nMr Sawaf to break this tightness then you will be given number of stretching to\r\ndo at home).</span><span lang=\"EN-GB\"> <b><i><span style=\"color:red\">See above.</span></i></b></span><b><i><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-family:&quot;Bookman Old Style&quot;,serif;color:red\"><o:p></o:p></span></i></b></p>', '/bench-daylight-daytime-1288484.jpg', '/knee_joint', '2019-04-28 08:01:06', '2019-04-28 08:01:06');
